dagger.internal

Class SetBinding<T>

  • java.lang.Object
    • dagger.internal.Binding<Set<T>>
      • dagger.internal.SetBinding<T>
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    MembersInjector<Set<T>>, javax.inject.Provider<Set<T>>

    public final class SetBinding<T>
extends Binding<Set<T>>
    A Binding<T> which contains contributors (other bindings marked with @Provides @OneOf), to which it delegates provision requests on an as-needed basis.

      • injectMembers

        public void injectMembers(Set<T> t)
        Description copied from interface: MembersInjector
        Injects dependencies into the fields and methods of instance. Ignores the presence or absence of an injectable constructor.

        Whenever the object graph creates an instance, it performs this injection automatically (after first performing constructor injection), so if you're able to let the object graph create all your objects for you, you'll never need to use this method.
